aston.group20.model

Class Counter

  • java.lang.Object
    • aston.group20.model.Counter

  • public class Counter
extends java.lang.Object
    The Counter class is used to store and display information regarding the Simulation; it is used for both the basic console interface as well as the short and long GUI reports.
    Version:
    1.0, April 2014
    Author:
    Group_20

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Counter()
      Creates a new Counter, which will call the clear method to ensure that all of the fields are reset to zero, ready for the Simulation to begin.

    • Method Summary

      Methods

      • incrementTotalPlanes

      • incrementWaitingTime

        public void incrementWaitingTime(int increment)
        Increments the waitingTime field, this is done when an Aircraft has taken off/landed/crashed, essentially when it has exited the Simulation so that we get it's true total waiting time.
        Parameters:
        increment - the waiting time of the Aircraft exiting the Simulation.

        public void setFlying(int flying)

      • setGrounded

        public void setGrounded(int grounded)
        This method sets the grounded field to equal the parameter value; it is called at each step of the Simulation, so that the statistics are up to date. It is identical in function to the setFlying(int) method.
        Parameters:
        grounded - the number of Aircraft on the ground in the current Simulation.

      • getGrounded

        public int getGrounded()
        Returns the number of Aircraft that are on the ground in the current Simulation.
        Returns:
        the number of Aircraft that are on the ground in the current Simulation.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        This method clears all of the fields, so that they are ready to be used for a new Simulation. It is called in the Counter() constructor.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        This method is called at the end of a Simulation to show summary information regarding the finished Simulation. It shows statistics that could be used to analyse the variables used and to choose the best/safest probabilities for the Simulation.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        summary information regarding the current, finished Simulation.

      • longReport

        public java.lang.String longReport()
        This method is called at every step of a Simulation in order to produce the longer report for the GUI; it shows information for every step of the Simulation, which could be used for a detailed analysis of the Simulation and to also find potential bugs.
        Returns:
        detailed information for each step of the Simulation.
